name: Lynx
summary: Multiple news sources report the capture of two lynxes in the Scottish Highlands following an illegal release. The captured animals were reportedly part of a conservation program in Spain, which aims to reintroduce the Iberian lynx to its former range. Authorities highlighted the dangers posed by approaching the predatory animals. The incident has sparked concerns about the potential impact on local wildlife and human safety, with calls for responsible conservation practices and strict penalties for illegal releases.

summary: Mick Lynch, the general secretary of the National Union of Rail, Maritime and Transport Workers (RMT), has announced his retirement after four years in the role. Lynch has been a vocal critic of the government's austerity policies and has led the RMT through a number of high-profile disputes with rail operators.
